snippet.textDisplay:
To Gilly's credit. He was excited for Raval when he got that wicket, part timer in a team clearly hurting, missing a strike bowler and trying "anything". He could have commentated in a completely patronising and mocking way. Instead, he did a great, unbiased and excited for a brilliant peice of cricket that sparked life back into the game, when the Aussies were just digging in & the two spinners were just plugging away.
Top bloke Gilly, top bloke!
